-- Lukoil Advances for Third Straight Day After Crude Oil Gains
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-02-14T11:40:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/lukoil-advances-for-third-straight-day-after-crude-oil-gains.html
OAO Lukoil (LKOH) ,  Russia ’s second-largest
oil producer, rose as much as 1 percent, gaining for the third
straight day, after oil prices advanced.  Lukoil climbed 0.9 percent to 1,862.10 rubles at 3:32 p.m.
in Moscow. OAO Rosneft, Russia’s largest oil producer, added 0.4
percent at 216.79 rubles a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 